    NWCA 2016 Wetland Indicator Status

    wisNWCA_2016.Rd

    A dataset containing NWCA 2016 USAC-specific Wetland Indicator Status values for vascular plant taxa

    wisNWCA_2016

    Format

    A data frame with 9584 observations on the following 5 variables.

    SPECIES_NAME_ID

    A numeric vector containing the NWCA taxonomic ID number

    NWCA_NAME

    Accepted USDA PLANTS name, or the official NWCA name where not available

    GEOG_ID

    Geographic unit to which value applies, which is US Army Corps region in this dataset

    WIS

    USAC-specific Wetland Indicator Status as used for NWCA 2016

    ECOIND1

    Wetland indicator status converted to numeric value, with lower numbers more characteristic of wetlands

    ECOIND2

    Wetland indicator status converted to numeric value, with higher numbers more characteristic of wetlands

    Note

    This dataset is the taxa list used for USAC-specific Wetland Indicator Status values used in NWCA 2016.

    Examples

    head(wisNWCA_2016)
#>   SPECIES_NAME_ID            NWCA_NAME   GEOG_ID WIS ECOIND1 ECOIND2
#> 1              58 xELYHORDEUM MACOUNII GT_PLAINS FAC       3       3
#> 2             129                ABIES    E_MTNS UND      NA      NA
#> 3             135       ABIES BALSAMEA    E_MTNS FAC       3       3
#> 4             135       ABIES BALSAMEA        NE FAC       3       3
#> 5             142       ABIES CONCOLOR    ARID_W UPL       5       1
#> 6             142       ABIES CONCOLOR    W_MTNS UPL       5       1
str(wisNWCA_2016)
#> 'data.frame':	9584 obs. of  6 variables:
#>  $ SPECIES_NAME_ID: int  58 129 135 135 142 142 146 153 153 155 ...
#>  $ NWCA_NAME      : chr  "xELYHORDEUM MACOUNII" "ABIES" "ABIES BALSAMEA" "ABIES BALSAMEA" ...
#>  $ GEOG_ID        : chr  "GT_PLAINS" "E_MTNS" "E_MTNS" "NE" ...
#>  $ WIS            : chr  "FAC" "UND" "FAC" "FAC" ...
#>  $ ECOIND1        : int  3 NA 3 3 5 5 4 4 4 4 ...
#>  $ ECOIND2        : int  3 NA 3 3 1 1 2 2 2 2 ...
